fields: You fought quite well, considering your wounds.
Access to this block is currently restricted to ensure safety.
All residents of this neighborhood are expected to evacuate immediately.
This is the Criminal Investigation Department,  part of the Public Safety Bureau.
Access to this block is currently restricted to ensure safety.
Excuse me! Are you Inspector Ginoza?
You've got rotten luck, having to deal with an incident right after getting posted.
I'm Tsunemori Akane. I've been assigned to the CID as of today.
Sorry, but the CID is very short on manpower.
So you'll have to hit the ground running.
A street scanner flagged him while doing a Hue Check, so a Security Drone ordered him to receive therapy, but he refused and ran.
The Psycho-Pass it recorded for him was forest green.
His aggression and compulsion are expected to be high.
Why would he avoid treatment long enough for his Hue to get this cloudy?
It's also possible that he used incompatible drugs.
In any case, he's a latent criminal; one far enough gone that we don't need to wait for Sibyl's Judgment.
The problem is that the place Okura ran to...
Since this is an abolition block, there's no relay device, so Drones can't come in.
In addition... I heard Okura abducted a passerby and is holding her hostage.
According to a witness, it's a young woman.
We haven't been able to confirm her identity yet.
Records state this is an uninhabited block, but because of that, it's become a den of homeless people.
Don't think that the guys you're about to meet are human like us.
Their Psycho-Pass Crime Coefficients all exceed a specific value.
They are people of bankrupt character.
Normally, they would be completely isolated as latent criminals, but they're allowed into the  outside world for the sole purpose
of flushing out criminals just like themselves.
They're beasts used to hunt beasts.
They're what we call Enforcers." They'll be your subordinates.
Is that cutie the newbie that everyone's been talking about, Gino?
Starting today, she's your second owner.
You guys all looked through the target's data, right?
We're going to tighten the noose around our cornered rat.
We'll divide into two groups and take turns.
Kunizuka and Kagari, come with me.
What?! I wanna go with the cutie!
It wasn't funny in the first place.
Well... Um... What should I do?
You could order us to stand by.
We wouldn't have any problems with that.
You oughta earn your paycheck, pops.
Hey, don't look so nervous, young lady.
You know how to use a Dominator, right?
I-I did receive training on it, more or less...
This is a gun that reads the Psycho-Pass of the target you're aiming at.
Its safety is released only when the target is a latent criminal.
You can just do what the Dominator tells you.
If it says shoot, just shoot.
If it's set to basic mode, it'll use Paralyzer.
It'll only paralyze the target, so we'll take them into custody and that'll be that.
Well, you don't have to take it too seriously.
It's a directional voice, so only the holder of the gun can hear it.
Don't worry about it. It might be annoying at first, but you'll get used to it soon.
Aren't we going to have a meeting and come up with a plan?
We'll hunt the prey and you'll observe.
That's all there is to it.
Um, could you go into a bit more detail?
What he's saying is, leave it to us.
We might not look like it, but we're experts.
We have our own way of doing things.
But the one who's responsible for our actions is you, the Inspector.
So if you have a problem with the way I do things, use that gun to shoot me.
We're latent criminals too, just like the target.
The Dominator will work on us as well.
Oh, we haven't introduced ourselves yet.
That stubborn fool is Kougami Shinya.
Looking forward to working with you, young lady.
Up until today, I did everything by the book.
I spent my whole life walking on eggshells, trying my hardest not to upset or bother anyone.
And yet, I get flagged by one little detector and boom!
They already treat me like I'm a criminal.
This is it for me. Now that it's come to this, it's all over.
I'll never be able to get a job, get married, or anything else.
I've restrained myself all this time. So now, I'll just do whatever I want. I'll take whatever I want.
I'll kill anyone I don't like!
to have sex with a pretty woman like you.
With a real, flesh-and-blood woman, not a virtual one.
They say you were the top student at the academy.
I'll give you some friendly advice.
Just forget everything you learned there.
None of that stuff is any use when you're actually working on a case.
Get used to it. Our work's full of things that defy all logic.
People's thoughts, wishes, hopes and desires...
We live in a time where technology can read everything in your mind, and yet, this place teems with people who hate, lie, steal, and try to harm others.
If that's not irrational, then what is it?
Everything you've been taught is based on theories and logic.
Soon, you'll likely come to realize how pointless they are.
I found the target on the fourth floor of the KT Building. What are your orders?
Stay there and keep an eye on him.
Hound 2 and I will box him in.
But considering how worked up he is, the girl he took as a hostage may be at the end of her rope.
Should I go in by myself and secure him?
My, my... What a bad boy.
An Oracle by the Sibyl System.
It says that Okura Nobuo is no longer someone who's needed in this world.
Oh no... All this because he was detected by a street scanner?
He probably drove himself into a corner.
Nothing, not even therapy, will work on him anymore.
The judgment on him is that there's no room for rehabilitation.
It's unfortunate that your first case had to be such an unpleasant one, young lady.
My Psycho-Pass has become so cloudy that it looks like mud.
What's more, your Psycho-Pass looks just like mine now.
If they catch you, it'll be all over for you too.
You'll be tortured by them as a latent criminal for the rest of your life.
We'd better resolve this quickly, or it'll be all over for the hostage.
Yeah. A Crime Coefficient can be contagious.
Young people these days aren't good at dealing with stress, so they're easily affected by violent urges and compulsions.
I wrote a thesis on that topic.
Let me tell you one thing, young lady. It could happen to any of us.
The reason we were made Enforcers in the first place is...
Using an old man and a newbie as a decoy, eh?
You sure got cojones, don't you, Kou?
We're with the Public Safety Bureau. You're safe now. Please rest at ease.
Calm down! We came to rescue you!
Well, I guess we have no choice.
That's exactly why the Paralyzer exists!
We'll put her to sleep right away and take her into custody!
You don't have to use violence on her!
Listen. The Dominators are Sibyl's eyes.
This town's system itself has decided that she's a threat!
So you'd shoot a victim who hasn't even committed a crime yet?! I can't accept that!
Stay away... Don't come any closer.
Or... this gun will kill you.
Please! I want to help you!
Tsunemori Akane, your Psycho-Pass Hue is powder blue this morning!
Have a wonderful day with that healthy mind of yours!
You're meeting up with Funahara Yuki and .Minase Kaori at Akebonobashi Station at 11:00.
At 14:30, you start second shift duty at the Public Safety Bureau.
Okay! I'll use the library as reference!
Your dietary intake yesterday was 2200 kilocalories in total.
The recommended amount for today's breakfast is 240 kilocalories.
I'll have a 200 kilocalorie Chinese-flavored breakfast.
It was my very first day on the job...
Today's weather will be morning clouds giving way to sunny skies.
There is a 0% chance of precipitation.
The anticipated group stress in the Shinjuku ward is Level 3.
I recommend taking a supplement to prevent mental contamination.
Yeah... though I can't give you the details
since I work for the Public Safety Bureau and all.
I don't know much about these things, but what you did wasn't in violation of your duties, right?
Then you don't have to worry about it, right?
Besides, your Psycho-Pass isn't that clouded either.
I guess that means you're not that bothered by it after all?
I didn't get a wink of sleep last night.
I'm surprised the Hue Check showed such a clear color for you, considering what you went through.
You don't give yourself much psychological care, and yet you're such a mental beauty.
How do you stay so healthy?
Well... Maybe I'm just thick-skinned, you know?
God really is unfair. You said it.
I-In any case... It's not that I doubt the Sibyl System, but I wonder if a career at the Public Safety Bureau is really right for me.
Jeez, you're lucky to even have the choice!
I know you like to speak without thinking, but that's pushing it even for you!
To start with, you were found to have an aptitude for jobs
at the Ministry of Economy and the Ministry of Technology, and yet you rejected them both and picked the Public Safety Bureau, right?
The best I could do was C-rank scores across the board.
What's the problem? You're good at blue-collar work.
I'm a systems engineer, so my shoulders are always killing me.
Akane, you were an honor student who scored 700 points on the last exam.
You should be able to take on any job with ease, right?
Sorry. I guess we went a little too far.
But I think that if anyone can pull off that job, it's you.
And not just because of the aptitude the System indicated.
As a friend, I know you'll do well.
That which needs to be done is carried out by those capable of doing it.
Such is the grace bestowed upon mankind by Sibyl."
I'm Tsunemori Akane. I've been assigned to the CID as of yesterday.
Oh! You're the new Inspector who shot Shinya, aren't you?
Wow... You're a lot cuter than I thought.
That cute face of yours hides how daring you can be, though!
What happened? Did Shinya grab your butt or something?
I was told I should come to you to find out how he's doing.
While I do have a physician's license, can you believe that's all it took for the government to delegate employee health care to the Analysis Lab?
Sure, I may be a latent criminal too, but that doesn't mean they can just slave drive me as much as they want, right?
R-Right... Let's see. Akane, was it?
If you're an Inspector, that puts you on the fast track at the Bureau, right?
Hurry up and become a high-ranking official so you can reform the system.
You can start by splashing out for a swimming pool and bar lounge at the CID.
Right, well... How's Kougami's treatment going?
Well, you scored a direct hit on his spinal cord, so he's still out of commission.
It'll be a little longer before he's able to stand, talk, or anything like that.
Of course, you wouldn't be able to join him in bed right now, either.
If you just want to peek in on him, that'd be okay. What do you wanna do?
W-Well, I'd better not bother him.
If he spends today resting, the aftereffects should go away.
Excuse me, are there any other tablets?
Enforcer Kougami is using the spare equipment.
...undergoing treatment after taking a Paralyzer on the chin? Yep!
Oh? You're on duty tonight, young lady?
It must be tough after what happened yesterday.
Well, let's hope that today's a little quieter
A Psycho-Pass above the regulation value has been detected
inside Iko Gryce Hill in the Adachi ward.
Inspector on duty, please accompany the Enforcers to the site immediately.

Well, our shift just ended, so... good luck.
Would you like me to cover for Kougami?
Drones have been watching the entrances to the mall since the warning was triggered.
In other words, whoever's elevating the Area Stress level is still in the mall.
Are we going to use Dominators?
We'll have them delivered to us as a precaution.
but we probably won't need them.
I thought your generation was used to playing with holo-suits on.
It feels a bit weird with my whole body as an Avatar.
It's okay, so let me see.
On the right, hiding behind the front column.
But... How can you tell without even using a scanner?
A beast can sniff out another beast's scent.
Excuse me. Could we please measure your Psycho-Pass?
My assessment is that you require emergency therapy.
So you really can identify latent criminals?
With experience, you'll intuitively know at first glance when someone's up to no good.
Committing crimes, or cracking down on them...
Either way, they're talents that deal with criminal behavior.
That's why my Crime Coefficient is so high.
Thanks to that, I'm now treated like a hunting dog who gets all the dirty work.
In the end... I was pretty useless in there, wasn't I?
Enforcers can't walk around outside without an accompanying Inspector.
After you bring Enforcers to the site, all you need to do is keep an eye on them to make sure  they don't slack off, run away or cause trouble for society.
That's all you need to do.
In other words, you're telling me not to do anything, right?
Can I join you, Ms. Inspector?
I thought you were already off duty today.
We Enforcers are prisoners, you know.
Even when we're off duty, there's nowhere else we can go besides the CID floor and our quarters.
As you can see, all the other women who work here are scary as hell, so...
I'm just glad that a cute girl like you joined the CID, Akane.
Oh, can I call you Akane?
But hell, an Inspector with the Public Safety Bureau? Crazy place to work, right?
Do you think I'm not suited for it?
After what happened yesterday, anyone would probably think that way.
Sibyl's Judgment of my job aptitude
exceeded the Bureau's employment standards, so here I am.
That's the thing I don't get.
If you passed the Bureau's standards, you must've gotten a good ranking for other places too, right?
Couldn't you have picked a different job? Yeah.
I got an A ranking for all thirteen ministries and agencies, not to mention six companies.
For all the other jobs, there were at least one or two people besides me
I was the only one who got an A ranking for the Public Safety Bureau.
There were more than 500 students and I was the only one.
So I thought that there must have been something that only I could do at the Bureau.
If I went there, I thought I could find my purpose in life...
I thought I'd be able to find out why I was born here and now.
I don't know. What makes you think that someone like me would have any idea?
You could choose any kind of life.
You've even agonized over it, right?
That's incredible. You're just like those old folk who lived in the days before Sibyl was created.
Nowadays, the Sibyl System reads your talent
and tells you the way of living that will bring you the most happiness.
And yet, you're talking about your purpose in life? The reason you were born?
I never even imagined there were people who stressed over things like that!
I was flagged in a Psycho-Pass test when I was five.
I've been a latent criminal ever since.
No possibility for rehabilitation through treatment.
And I'd much rather be one of the Bureau's hunting dogs
and take on assassination jobs than spend the rest of my life in an isolation facility.
That was the only choice I had.
I wasn't planning to be mean to you or anything, but I changed my mind. So I'll ask you again.
Why did you become an Inspector?
You don't see many Inspectors who'd apologize to an Enforcer.
I have no right to complain.
Did I just stand in everyone's way and put them in danger?
I've been an Enforcer for a long time.
The hunting dogs' behavior of following orders to take down prey with neither hesitation nor doubt
I just followed that gun's orders, and shot many latent criminals.
It was for the good of society, I told myself.
It was easier to just accept that logic without question, and past a certain point I didn't even think about it anymore.
I didn't even think to look back at myself and what I was doing.
Being a detective isn't about bringing people down.
It's supposed to be about protecting people.
You decided what was right on your own.
You were able to put justice before your duty.
With a boss like you, I might be able to work as a detective, not just a dog.
You also don't see many Inspectors who'd bow to an Enforcer.
If you had time to think about it with a level head, you would've tried not to shoot her, right?
I didn't hesitate at the time.
I thought I'd die if I hesitated.
I thought, I don't want to die in a place like this.
I cannot die here, no matter what!"
I have unfinished business to take care of.
There's something I have to settle no matter what!
So, you're saying that you made the right decision at the time?
Is that your conclusion, Inspector Tsunemori?
Yes. Her Crime Coefficient was only temporarily elevated.
In fact, the therapy she's receiving after being taken into custody is going well, and her Psycho-Pass is recovering.
Kougami, is there anything you want to say?
No. Inspector Tsunemori fulfilled her duty.
The victim is Shioyama Daisuke, twenty-seven years old.
He worked at the Hachiouji Drone Factory.
His body was found at precisely 4 AM.
They said he was dismembered by a Drone he was testing.
Do you think... it was an accident?
I heard that this is already the third casualty in the past year at this factory.
The body was found in the Drones' behavior inspection section, the only manned area in the otherwise automated production line.
There are about fifty debuggers working there around the clock.
that need to be evaluated and verified each month.
They have no choice but to work around the clock.
If you can install a program that induces a malfunction in a Drone before it's tested, there's a good chance you can make it look like an accident. Which means...
This could be a murder case.
But if there are only fifty suspects, can't we just check everyone's Crime Coefficient?
I feel like I'll be able to get along well with the Enforcers.
Do you mean you'll get along with them as a colleague?
They say that fools learn from their experiences, while the wise learn from history.
I hope you're not a fool.
I'd like to see where it happened.
We do a safety check and a test run here after the Drones are built.
We depend on machines for all the other processes, but the final check still needs to be done by humans, as it's always been.
As you can see, it's dangerous work.
It's hard on the debuggers, isn't it?
In fact, there aren't many ways to deal with stress here, unlike in the outside world.
You can't connect to the net, so there's not much in the way of diversions.
We're not wired for it, and this building itself is an anechoic chamber, so there's no way to access outside communications networks here.
This is the most efficient security system against hacking.
How horrifying. A totally isolated area, huh?
The body was already taken away by a Drone during the initial response.
However, I'm told it was all recorded on this disk.
It's like his body was dissected by the Drone while he was still alive. Nasty.
Did the victim, Mr. Shioyama, have anyone with a grudge against him? No, he didn't.
His Psycho-Pass showed no indication of any problems.
It must have been an accident.
But this is the third incident of this kind. Don't you think that's a few too many?
As I told you earlier, this is a dangerous work environment.
If you have any criticisms regarding our management, we're all ears, but please air those concerns through the appropriate channels.
What about the Drone that went out of control?
I'm having it sent to headquarters.
We'll have to wait for Karanomori to complete her analysis, but I was told that its memory, including the backup, is gone.
For now, head back to the car and forward this to headquarters.
I have a few more things to talk about with Chief Goda.
These are the Psycho-Passes for all staff within this facility.
These records contain the results of our detailed periodic checks along with the Hue Assessments by the scanners installed in the building. Thank you.
As you can see for yourself, there are no staff members who continuously exceeded the regulation limit.
Even if you suspect murder, there's no suspect to be found.
We won't know that until we analyze this data using the Sibyl System.
But there's an easier way to check.
Please have all the staff come outside the anechoic chamber
and let us check them using our devices.
People's lives are at stake here.
If you can provide evidence that Shioyama's death was a murder, we will certainly cooperate with you.
But as things stand, we have no choice but to consider this an accident.
If you want to investigate our staff even to the point of disrupting production, please file a request with the Ministry of Economy first.
I bet Nobuchika's trying to put some pressure on that chief right now.
You saw the documents too, right?
This is a government facility under the jurisdiction of the Ministry of Economy.
And government offices always look out for their own bottom lines.
So they don't want anyone interfering enough to cause a drop in productivity.
Even though someone lost their life?
That's exactly why they want it to be declared an accident as soon as possible.
But their scanner hasn't actually detected anyone dangerous, right?

If you want to actually compute a person's mental state based on the cymatic scan data
in order to check their job aptitude and Crime Coefficient, you need to wait in line for an analysis by the Sibyl System.
However, our Dominators are able to cut in line,  so to speak, and request an analysis immediately.
That's why they can see right through someone's mind
with no time lag as soon as you point the gun at them. But...
Since this facility blocks all electromagnetic radiation, we won't be able to connect to the Sibyl System while inside.
And without that, your Dominator's basically just scrap iron.
I wonder what the chances are.
You mean the chance that his death was an accident?
Ha! It was hard not to laugh. No kidding.
If your intuition didn't tell you that the moment you saw him, you're no detective.
I'm sure all the Enforcers had a gut feeling.
That was a murder. No doubt about it. I wonder what the motive was.
Based on the victim's condition, I'm guessing...
Man, this place must really suck to work at.
I can't imagine being stuck in an offline environment in this day and age.
But the Psycho-Pass Hues for the workers here are rather stable.
No matter where you are, people find ways to entertain themselv How's it going?
No. The data you gave us showed nothing unusual
Hey, yellow-green. Gonna have lunch in your fancy private room again today?
What are they doing? That's terrible!
Oh, that. You can just leave them be. Huh?
Since this is an environment with few diversions, we need someone to keep the others entertained, you know? But isn't he...
If his Psycho-Pass gets cloudy enough to be an issue, we'll assign him somewhere else right away.
As I told you, we take great care in managing the  psychological state of our employees.
This man has his own role to play, same as anyone else.
Sibyl might've recommended this workplace to him
because he was best suited for this purpose.
And I guess someone like you,  who can laugh and turn a blind eye, is best suited to run this place.
What a blessing the Sibyl System is, huh?
If what that chief guy said is true, there's always one person whose Hue Check gets worse over time.
And this person is later transferred somewhere else without exception.
However, no one has been reassigned for the past year.
The deaths started happening a year ago, right?
And for that past year, the same person has been the target of bullying.
Other people's Psycho-Passes show clear colors, but there's one person whose Psycho-Pass is clouded.
Ah! Kanehara Yuji. This Hue Assessment shows yellow-green.
I see. That explains his nickname.
Seems like the Hue Assessment results are open to everyone here. This is crazy.
But this guy's latest measurement shows an improved Hue.
In fact, his Hue was the cloudiest... on the day before Shioyama died.
Can't be... That doesn't make sense.
Why would a person's Psycho-Pass improve after killing someone?
The other employees have all been taking out their stress on Kanehara himself.
It's not that strange when you think about it.

Is this more of that detective's intuition"  you're always talking about?
It proves that latent criminals like you are the dregs of society!
We can't act on some speculation based on circumstantial evidence.
Our job... is to maintain an orderly society based on the Crime Coefficients judged by Sibyl.
The kind of order where three people die in one year?
I'll find out whether Kanehara is the killer. I'll have conclusive evidence before you kn Enough already!
Inspector Ginoza, may I speak to you?
I'd rather try Kougami's plan than risk letting a crime go unsolved.
You're the one who's acting strange here!
Did something happen between you and Masaoka?
I... I can do a better job working with the Enforcers!

If you think you can keep those hunting dogs under control, you're welcome to try.

Did something happen between Ginoza and Masaoka?
Wait, Akane, don't tell me you seriously asked Gino that to his face?!
You really shouldn't have brought that up. What?

The furthest they'll reach is the elevator hall on the second floor.
Can you bring Kanehara out there?
You're just gonna talk to him, right?

Does your food taste better with blood on your hands?
Shioyama, Asami, and Koriyama... You killed them all, didn't you?!

showed that the toilet in this apartment has been broken for the past two months.
